      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_022203357.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_021803352.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7035"> </a>Before assembling the slider with the outer sleeve, lubricate the bush sliding surfaces with fork oil.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7038"> </a>Push the bush (20) and collar (22) into the outer sleeve (18) using the seal driving tool (A), part no. <span class="bold">88713.3204</span>.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7043"> </a>Drive the sealing ring (24) into the outer tube using the same tool.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7045"> </a>Fit the snap ring (19) and the dust seal (23).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_022303359.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7050"> </a>The outer sleeve must smoothly slide on slider. Support with your hands only the sliders and outer sleeves in order to avoid
         damaging the seals and guiding bushings.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7053"> </a>Insert the complete damper cartridge (9) into slider (15), and tighten tool <span class="bold">88713.3203</span> to cartridge.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_022403361.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7061"> </a>Install seal (17) and compression adjuster screw (16), and tighten fully home.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_021403348.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7066"> </a>Fill half the recommended quantity of fluid in each leg "<a href="50534.html#DUC5aa22028296e10058f9c817c5ab0d2d2">Fluids and lubricants</a>".
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7071"> </a>Pump using tool <span class="bold">88713.3203</span> to allow fluid to fill all the volume.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7076"> </a>Slide both the damping cartridge and outer sleeve fully down the inner tube.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7078"> </a>Pour the remaining oil into the fork leg and measure the oil level.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/important.jpg">Important
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7081"> </a>Keep the fork leg vertical when measuring the oil level. Make sure the oil level is the same in both fork legs.
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7085"> </a>Recommended oil:
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7087"> </a>SHELL ADVANCE FORK 7.5 or DONAX TA.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7089"> </a>Standard capacity:
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7091"> </a>720 cc per leg.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7094"> </a>The quantity of oil affects fork response during the final part of the compression stroke.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7096"> </a>High oil level increases compression loading, low oil level will decrease it.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7098"> </a>Clean off any oil from the spring (10) and the lock nut (8) before refitting.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7101"> </a>Install the following parts: washer (13) and preload tube (12).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7103"> </a>Fit spring (10), bush (11) and lock nut (8): install bush (11) with the taper side facing the lock nut (8).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_021103338.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_021003337.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_020803336.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7112"> </a>Screw the lock nut (8) onto the cartridge (9) with a hexagon wrench.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_020703335.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7117"> </a>Using the same wrench, hold the lock nut and screw the top plug (7) complete with the O-ring onto the cartridge (9).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e7119"> </a>Tighten top plug (7) fully home.
         </div>
      </div>
